Package edu.missouri.drone.static_height

A collection of static-height, offline coverage path planning algorithms. These are taken from the literature and many of them were initially conceived for ground robots.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BoustrophedonDrone
    An offline drone which splits complex polygons into simpler ones using a vertical sweeping line, then covers each with a plow traversal.
    CombinatoryJiaoDrone
    An offline drone which splits complex polygons into simpler ones by splitting concave vertices, applying Jiao's cellular decomposition algorithm.
    DevDrone  
    HuangDrone
    An offline drone which splits complex polygons into simpler ones by splitting concave vertices using Huang's cellular decomposition.
    JiaoDrone
    An offline drone which splits complex polygons into simpler ones by splitting concave vertices using a minimalized version of Jiao's cellular decomposition.
    JiaoDrone.Reordering
    An arrangement of polygonal regions associated with some cost.
    NullDrone  
    OfflineDrone
    An abstract drone, one that does not make changes to its path during the traversal.
    OracleDrone  
    PathTransformDrone
    An offline drone which decomposes an area into a grid, then traverses the area cell by cell according to each cell's distance from an end point and the edges of the area.
    PlowDrone
    An offline drone which traverses an area using a simple back-and-forth motion.
    UnwisePlowDrone
    An offline drone that traverses a polygon in the worst way.
